1
00:00:38,420 --> 00:00:41,060
=How to Train Your Killer=

2
00:00:41,060 --> 00:00:43,900
=Episode 23=

3
00:00:46,420 --> 00:00:47,260
Sorry.

4
00:00:47,700 --> 00:00:49,660
Your invitation is a forgery.

5
00:00:51,820 --> 00:00:52,940
A forgery?

6
00:00:53,420 --> 00:00:54,420
That's impossible.

7
00:00:54,420 --> 00:00:56,100
A fake? That's so unreliable.

8
00:00:56,100 --> 00:00:56,940
Indeed.

9
00:00:57,180 --> 00:00:58,940
The Sky Pavilion's auction

10
00:00:59,340 --> 00:01:01,740
is a grand event held every three years.

11
00:01:02,420 --> 00:01:03,340
Seats are limited.

12
00:01:04,020 --> 00:01:06,300
So it's no surprise some shady folks
forge invitations.

13
00:01:06,540 --> 00:01:08,900
Best keep your eyes sharp.

14
00:01:09,100 --> 00:01:10,180
Or you might get swindled.

15
00:01:11,140 --> 00:01:12,860
Scheming ticket peddlers.

16
00:01:14,500 --> 00:01:15,340
In that case…

17
00:01:16,940 --> 00:01:19,060
You still recognize me, right?

18
00:01:23,740 --> 00:01:24,780
Aren't you

19
00:01:24,780 --> 00:01:26,140
Yuan Chen

20
00:01:26,540 --> 00:01:27,900
whom we blacklisted long ago?

21
00:01:28,180 --> 00:01:29,020
You!

22
00:01:30,110 --> 00:01:30,980
How's that?

23
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:32,380
Told you it wasn't reliable.

24
00:01:38,020 --> 00:01:39,180
(Crown Prince's Token)

25
00:01:41,020 --> 00:01:42,420
The Crown Prince's Token?

26
00:01:42,420 --> 00:01:43,260
Exactly.

27
00:01:44,580 --> 00:01:46,260
Now we can get inside, right?

28
00:01:46,300 --> 00:01:47,140
Of course you can.

29
00:01:47,300 --> 00:01:48,140
Naturally.

30
00:01:48,580 --> 00:01:50,020
Please, come in. This way.

31
00:01:54,900 --> 00:01:55,740
Please, come in.

32
00:01:57,380 --> 00:02:01,780
(Sky Pavilion)

33
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:07,380
Welcome, honored guests.

34
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:15,160
What do you think of this place?

35
00:02:22,020 --> 00:02:22,860
Let's go.

36
00:02:23,100 --> 00:02:23,940
Come on, let's move.

37
00:02:38,460 --> 00:02:39,620
Welcome, honored guests,

38
00:02:39,860 --> 00:02:41,540
to Sky Pavilion today

39
00:02:41,820 --> 00:02:43,180
and to attend the Treasure Auction

40
00:02:43,180 --> 00:02:44,460
held every three years.

41
00:02:45,260 --> 00:02:47,620
Believe me, the treasures
of Sky Pavilion

42
00:02:47,620 --> 00:02:49,180
will certainly not disappoint everyone.

43
00:02:49,700 --> 00:02:50,820
Well then, no more idle talk.

44
00:02:51,380 --> 00:02:54,220
The Treasure Auction shall now commence.

45
00:02:55,460 --> 00:02:57,460
- Good, good!
- Excellent!

46
00:02:59,060 --> 00:03:00,240
Our first treasure on display

47
00:03:00,300 --> 00:03:02,130
is a statue of Guanyin
carved from green jade.

48
00:03:05,420 --> 00:03:07,660
Starting bid: 1,000 taels of silver.

49
00:03:08,940 --> 00:03:10,660
A green jade Guanyin statue?

50
00:03:11,100 --> 00:03:12,860
Such an extravagant opening bid!

51
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:14,990
(Number 14)
2,000 taels.

52
00:03:15,300 --> 00:03:16,140
2,000 taels.

53
00:03:17,060 --> 00:03:18,060
2,000, going once.

54
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:19,330
(Number 6)
5,000 taels.

55
00:03:19,420 --> 00:03:20,260
5,000 taels.

56
00:03:20,780 --> 00:03:21,820
Any further bids?

57
00:03:22,420 --> 00:03:23,420
The very first treasure

58
00:03:23,420 --> 00:03:24,820
has already soared to 5,000 taels.

59
00:03:24,980 --> 00:03:26,060
Do we have enough silver?

60
00:03:27,780 --> 00:03:28,780
5,000 taels, going once.

61
00:03:29,220 --> 00:03:30,260
5,000 taels, going twice.

62
00:03:30,860 --> 00:03:31,980
Any higher offers?

63
00:03:33,980 --> 00:03:35,260
5,000 taels, sold!

64
00:03:35,460 --> 00:03:36,300
Deal!

65
00:03:39,660 --> 00:03:41,140
3,500 taels of silver.

66
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:42,220
(Number 22)
4,000 taels.

67
00:03:42,340 --> 00:03:43,340
(Number 26)
6,500 taels.

68
00:03:43,340 --> 00:03:44,330
(Number 14)
7,000 taels.

69
00:03:44,330 --> 00:03:45,100
Deal!

70
00:03:45,300 --> 00:03:46,220
Starting bid.

71
00:03:46,250 --> 00:03:47,820
- 4,000 taels of silver.
- So stunning.

72
00:03:47,820 --> 00:03:48,800
(Number 14)
7,000 taels.

73
00:03:52,780 --> 00:03:53,820
A jade pillow?

74
00:03:55,140 --> 00:03:56,060
Such a large piece.

75
00:03:56,460 --> 00:03:57,460
Starting bid:

76
00:03:57,620 --> 00:03:59,140
4,000 taels of silver.

77
00:04:03,220 --> 00:04:04,660
Come on, with so many treasures here,

78
00:04:04,660 --> 00:04:05,940
how can you still be dozing off?

79
00:04:08,620 --> 00:04:09,460
Wake up!

80
00:04:10,940 --> 00:04:12,260
Now, the next treasure

81
00:04:12,340 --> 00:04:13,540
is worth a great deal.

82
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:15,020
Bring it over.

83
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:18,620
This is Master Qinghe's original work.

84
00:04:18,780 --> 00:04:20,820
The seventh scroll
in the Twelve Lotus series.

85
00:04:20,860 --> 00:04:22,460
Lotus After the Rain.

86
00:04:35,860 --> 00:04:36,700
Father,

87
00:04:37,140 --> 00:04:38,580
what is this?

88
00:04:39,140 --> 00:04:40,100
This is

89
00:04:40,540 --> 00:04:41,500
a lotus.

90
00:04:48,740 --> 00:04:51,020
(Zhou Yulian)

91
00:04:52,340 --> 00:04:54,780
As in my mother's name?

92
00:04:56,340 --> 00:04:57,820
Clever girl, Qingyao.

93
00:04:58,340 --> 00:04:59,340
This character

94
00:04:59,500 --> 00:05:01,130
is the same one
as in your mother's name.

95
00:05:01,460 --> 00:05:02,420
Yulian

96
00:05:02,580 --> 00:05:03,460
means

97
00:05:03,460 --> 00:05:05,820
a lotus after the rain.

98
00:05:07,820 --> 00:05:09,700
Yulian.

99
00:05:13,860 --> 00:05:19,100
(Zhou Yulian)

100
00:05:21,460 --> 00:05:23,620
Father, why are you crying?

101
00:05:23,660 --> 00:05:25,100
Are you feeling unwell?

102
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:26,940
Pain, pain, fly away.

103
00:05:26,940 --> 00:05:27,980
It's alright. Don't worry.

104
00:05:29,420 --> 00:05:30,420
I'm fine.

105
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:33,220
I...

106
00:05:35,140 --> 00:05:36,020
I just...

107
00:05:37,740 --> 00:05:38,900
Miss your mother.

108
00:05:56,380 --> 00:05:58,580
This painting is the only one
in the Twelve Lotus series

109
00:05:58,780 --> 00:06:01,060
that has not been collected by anyone.

110
00:06:01,220 --> 00:06:02,420
Its value is extremely high.

111
00:06:02,700 --> 00:06:04,820
Starting bid: 7,000 taels of silver.

112
00:06:05,860 --> 00:06:06,940
7,000 taels?

113
00:06:15,380 --> 00:06:16,220
7,000 taels.

114
00:06:17,260 --> 00:06:18,600
We came here for the stone.

115
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:20,440
- Why bid for a painting?
- 7,000. Going once.

116
00:06:20,460 --> 00:06:21,860
Any higher offers?

117
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:23,990
(Number 22)
8,000 taels.

118
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:24,860
8,000 taels.

119
00:06:24,870 --> 00:06:25,860
(Number 14)
9,000 taels.

120
00:06:25,860 --> 00:06:26,850
9,000 taels.

121
00:06:26,860 --> 00:06:27,700
- 10,000!
- 10,000!

122
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:29,140
10,000 taels for a painting?

123
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:30,900
(Number 3)
11,000 taels.

124
00:06:30,900 --> 00:06:32,580
You, a swordsman, bidding for art?

125
00:06:32,660 --> 00:06:33,620
What's gotten into you?

126
00:06:33,780 --> 00:06:35,220
Any higher offers?

127
00:06:35,420 --> 00:06:36,340
13,000 taels.

128
00:06:36,460 --> 00:06:37,820
13,000 taels.

129
00:06:38,540 --> 00:06:39,580
20,000 taels!

130
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:41,890
(Number 3)
20,000 taels!

131
00:06:41,900 --> 00:06:42,780
Now that's true taste.

132
00:06:43,340 --> 00:06:44,580
20,000, going once.

133
00:06:44,860 --> 00:06:45,860
20,000, going twice.

134
00:06:46,060 --> 00:06:47,420
20,000, sold!

135
00:06:49,300 --> 00:06:50,960
I really don't know what
to say about you.

136
00:06:56,580 --> 00:06:57,420
Your painting.

137
00:06:59,380 --> 00:07:00,220
Much appreciated.

138
00:07:10,780 --> 00:07:12,460
The next treasure

139
00:07:12,740 --> 00:07:14,340
is rather peculiar.

140
00:07:14,540 --> 00:07:16,580
I daresay none of you
have ever seen its like.

141
00:07:16,860 --> 00:07:18,300
- Thanks.
- Bring it over.

142
00:07:23,580 --> 00:07:24,580
What is that?

143
00:07:24,620 --> 00:07:25,580
No idea.

144
00:07:30,980 --> 00:07:33,140
This should be the celestial stone.

145
00:07:33,140 --> 00:07:33,980
Look.

146
00:07:35,220 --> 00:07:38,220
This item is the celestial stone.

147
00:07:38,340 --> 00:07:39,740
It's just a rock, isn't it?

148
00:07:39,740 --> 00:07:40,980
What's so special about it?

149
00:07:42,900 --> 00:07:43,980
You don't know its worth.

150
00:07:44,460 --> 00:07:45,140
This stone

151
00:07:45,140 --> 00:07:46,700
was found by a herdsman on the border,

152
00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:48,180
at the foot of the Tianshan Mountains.

153
00:07:48,180 --> 00:07:49,780
It is said to come from beyond the sky.

154
00:07:51,380 --> 00:07:52,940
Everyone, please stay calm.

155
00:07:53,220 --> 00:07:55,020
In a moment, I'll show you

156
00:07:55,020 --> 00:07:56,220
what makes it extraordinary.

157
00:07:59,020 --> 00:08:00,300
I'm a little nervous.

158
00:08:02,980 --> 00:08:03,940
What are they doing?

159
00:08:05,220 --> 00:08:06,060
Take a look.

160
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:14,460
It really sparks with energy!

161
00:08:14,980 --> 00:08:16,140
Truly remarkable.

162
00:08:23,220 --> 00:08:24,060
Indeed.

163
00:08:24,300 --> 00:08:25,860
This celestial stone

164
00:08:25,860 --> 00:08:27,380
is surrounded by the power of thunder.

165
00:08:27,660 --> 00:08:30,660
Perhaps more of its wonders
remain undiscovered.

166
00:08:31,060 --> 00:08:33,020
You may bid for it,

167
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,320
and study it at your leisure.

168
00:08:34,340 --> 00:08:35,580
The auction begins now.

169
00:08:35,860 --> 00:08:37,980
Starting bid: 3,000 taels of silver.

170
00:08:39,620 --> 00:08:40,660
Hold on.

171
00:08:40,700 --> 00:08:42,040
Let's see how things unfold first.

172
00:08:42,100 --> 00:08:43,040
The more eager you seem,

173
00:08:43,040 --> 00:08:44,570
the more they'll think it's a treasure.

174
00:08:44,570 --> 00:08:46,140
It doesn't look useful at all.

175
00:08:46,150 --> 00:08:47,420
It can't be forged into a weapon,

176
00:08:47,420 --> 00:08:48,360
nor used to heal wounds.

177
00:08:49,220 --> 00:08:50,780
At best, you could use it to shock fish.

178
00:08:53,580 --> 00:08:54,740
3,500 taels!

179
00:08:55,140 --> 00:08:56,620
3,500 taels of silver.

180
00:08:57,540 --> 00:08:58,700
No more bids?

181
00:08:59,340 --> 00:09:00,660
3,500 taels.

182
00:09:01,530 --> 00:09:02,830
3,500 taels.

183
00:09:03,460 --> 00:09:05,020
This is a stone from beyond the heavens.

184
00:09:05,420 --> 00:09:07,620
It might well be the highlight

185
00:09:07,620 --> 00:09:08,500
of this auction.

186
00:09:08,660 --> 00:09:09,700
With something this rare,

187
00:09:09,780 --> 00:09:11,100
why not keep it for yourself?

188
00:09:11,300 --> 00:09:12,340
Who are you trying to fool?

189
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:14,300
Exactly.

190
00:09:14,300 --> 00:09:15,340
Who are you trying to fool?

191
00:09:16,410 --> 00:09:17,660
If that's the case,

192
00:09:18,780 --> 00:09:20,780
3,500 taels, going once.

193
00:09:20,980 --> 00:09:23,260
3,500 taels, going twice.

194
00:09:23,380 --> 00:09:24,340
(Number 3)
4,000 taels.

195
00:09:24,540 --> 00:09:25,380
4,000 taels.

196
00:09:25,740 --> 00:09:26,700
4,000 taels.

197
00:09:27,180 --> 00:09:28,420
Any higher offers?

198
00:09:36,100 --> 00:09:37,060
10,000 taels.

199
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:43,700
He lost his mind?

200
00:09:45,420 --> 00:09:46,260
Come on.

201
00:09:46,540 --> 00:09:48,020
Who does this guy come from?

202
00:09:49,100 --> 00:09:50,100
15,000 taels.

203
00:09:51,060 --> 00:09:52,220
20,000 taels.

204
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:54,580
30,000 taels.

205
00:09:55,860 --> 00:09:56,700
50,000 taels.

206
00:09:56,800 --> 00:09:58,380
- 50,000 taels.
- It's getting heated.

207
00:09:58,420 --> 00:09:59,460
50,000, going once.

208
00:09:59,660 --> 00:10:00,820
50,000, going twice.

209
00:10:01,180 --> 00:10:02,300
50,000, sold.

210
00:10:02,580 --> 00:10:03,420
Deal!

211
00:10:05,900 --> 00:10:06,860
Who exactly is this man?

212
00:10:06,860 --> 00:10:07,980
Congratulations to you.

213
00:10:08,220 --> 00:10:09,800
- He knows the stone's power.
- Serve it

214
00:10:09,800 --> 00:10:11,060
to the guest upstairs.

215
00:10:11,220 --> 00:10:12,220
Impossible.

216
00:10:13,700 --> 00:10:14,620
What do we do now?

217
00:10:16,020 --> 00:10:17,620
The auction's meaningless at this point.

218
00:10:17,980 --> 00:10:18,820
Follow him later.

219
00:10:19,580 --> 00:10:20,420
Mm.

220
00:10:30,100 --> 00:10:31,100
Next up

221
00:10:31,140 --> 00:10:33,820
is the grand finale of this auction:

222
00:10:34,860 --> 00:10:36,540
the masterpiece sword 'Frostfree,'

223
00:10:36,540 --> 00:10:38,900
forged with blood
by the master swordsmith Mo Feng.

224
00:10:41,620 --> 00:10:42,460
Let's go.

225
00:10:45,420 --> 00:10:46,260
Go.

226
00:10:46,580 --> 00:10:49,020
Starting bid: 5,000 taels of silver.

227
00:11:18,380 --> 00:11:19,220
Come out.

228
00:11:31,460 --> 00:11:34,060
♪When a breeze passes by♪

229
00:11:34,580 --> 00:11:37,900
♪The sand and wind burn with longing♪

230
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:40,540
♪Fearless even when thirst
goes unquenched♪

231
00:11:40,860 --> 00:11:44,020
♪Like a camel wandering
with eyes closed♪

232
00:11:44,380 --> 00:11:47,340
♪When the rain quietly settles♪

233
00:11:47,340 --> 00:11:50,660
♪I think of our sorrow yet unknown♪

234
00:11:50,860 --> 00:11:53,580
♪No need to hum the song of the wind♪

235
00:11:53,740 --> 00:11:57,380
♪Ignoring the sky darkening before us♪

236
00:11:57,540 --> 00:11:59,140
♪I finally understood that truth♪

237
00:11:59,140 --> 00:12:00,620
♪Yet you have already faded away♪

238
00:12:00,820 --> 00:12:02,460
♪I lose my way in the night♪

239
00:12:02,460 --> 00:12:03,940
♪Not knowing how to still my heart♪

240
00:12:03,940 --> 00:12:05,620
♪Loving you feels like lifetimes apart♪

241
00:12:05,620 --> 00:12:08,580
♪Yet longing flows back into verse♪

242
00:12:09,020 --> 00:12:11,460
♪For you and me to meet again♪

243
00:12:11,900 --> 00:12:14,740
♪We must cross a thousand years
of promises♪

244
00:12:15,020 --> 00:12:17,100
♪In the pouring rain♪

245
00:12:17,100 --> 00:12:21,460
♪As if you are still by my side♪
